Reducing restrictive practice worldwide is so important, collaboration, trust + understanding - including the use of de-escalation MUST be at the forefront of ALL care and support for people with a learning disability. Restraint should always be a last resort to maintain safety!!

upon researching, the devices have been used when Positive Behavioural  Supoort pathways have been insufficient. PBS done correctly, collaboratively and with constant evaluation would NOT warrant punitive and abusive practice!!!! Consistency, proactive strategies and more are KEY
